cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image classifiers and autoencoders. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it proposes a novel way to measure and understand convolutional neural networks. Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it deals with deep learning models. The paper also involves measuring the mutual information between original images and auto-encoded reconstructions, which could fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper could be classified under natural language processing (cs.CL) as autoencoders are commonly used in text data processing.
